description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and their families have increased access to nutrition and health services in targeted municipalities., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Social Protection, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 children, adolescents, youth and their families, especially the most disadvantaged, are increasingly using improved quality basic services.
